    "w uv = 1; ∀{u, v} ∈ E.Using Equation (11) followed by Equation (10), we can writeE w [⟨C(γ)⟩] E w {u,v}∈E w uv = 2 N (D + 1)µ E w [⟨C(γ)⟩] = 1 2 + 1 2µ E w [w sin(wγ)] (E w [cos(wγ)]) D (19) = 1 2 + ϑ 1 (D, γ) √ D, (20)where we introduce ϑ 1 (D, γ) to match Π * in Equation (5).",
    "We will now show that ϑ 1 (D, γ) tends to a D-independent quantity as D → ∞ when γ = Θ(D -1/2), and use the resulting limit to derive the optimal value γ * in the limit of infinite-sized graphs.The assumption of γ = Θ(D -1/2) is inspired by the numerical observation that the optimal γ for unweighted MaxCut is Θ(D -1/2) (see, e.g."
